

=Description=

Undertaken by Paul Atkinson:

"two Post Industrial Manufacturing research projects,
Automake and FutureFactories. 

Both of these
systems utilize computer generated random elements
and consumer decision-making processes within flexible
schemes defined by a designer and a craftsman/
maker. The results have changed the perceptions of
consumers towards the products that they create and
the processes of design, as well as their perceptions of
their own capabilities. The systems not only liberate
the designer from the sterile perfection of the manufactured
form, but also free the consumer from the
dictatorship of owning identical products. Clearly,
Post Industrial Manufacturing systems will change
the meaning of design."
(http://issuu.com/openp2pdesign/docs/cis.doc_open-design)


